and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":20},{"title":"esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3","target":"esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3","line":20},{"title":"hoverboard-bldc-hub-motor-250w-36v-with-hall-sensors","target":"hoverboard-bldc-hub-motor-250w-36v-with-hall-sensors","line":20},{"title":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","target":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","line":20},{"title":"raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3","target":"raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3","line":20},{"title":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","target":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","line":20},{"title":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","target":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","line":21},{"title":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","target":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","line":31},{"title":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","target":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","line":33},{"title":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","target":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","line":91},{"title":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","target":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","line":92},{"title":"hoverboard-bldc-hub-motor-250w-36v-with-hall-sensors","target":"hoverboard-bldc-hub-motor-250w-36v-with-hall-sensors","line":93},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":94},{"title":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":95},{"title":"esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3","target":"esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3","line":96},{"title":"raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3","target":"raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3","line":97},{"title":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","target":"hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based","line":98},{"title":"ws2812b-neopixel-ring-status-led-array-for-system-feedback","target":"ws2812b-neopixel-ring-status-led-array-for-system-feedback","line":99},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":102},{"title":"passives","target":"passives","line":103}],"metadata":{"description":"TI TXS0108E 8-channel auto-direction-sensing level shifter — TSSOP-20 package on breakout board. Faster than BSS138-based shifters (up to 110Mbps push-pull, 1.2Mbps open-drain). Used for Hall sensor signals between 5V BLDC controllers and 3.3V ESP32","topics":["[[shields]]","[[passives]]"],"status":"verified","quantity":1,"voltage":[1.2,3.3,5],"interfaces":["Digital"],"logic_level":"mixed","logic_notes":"Bridge-style shifter. A-side follows the low-voltage rail and B-side follows the high-voltage rail. Best for push-pull digital signals, not open-drain I2C.","manufacturer":"Texas Instruments","part_number":"TXS0108E","pinout":"TXS0108E breakout (TSSOP-20):\nVCCA  → Low-voltage side (1.2-3.6V, typically 3.3V from ESP32)\nVCCB  → High-voltage side (1.65-5.5V, typically 5V from controller)\nGND   → Common ground (shared between both sides)\nOE    → Output enable (active HIGH, connect to VCCA for always-on)\nA1-A8 → Low-voltage side channels (connect to 3.3V MCU)\nB1-B8 → High-voltage side channels (connect to 5V device)\n","compatible_with":["[[nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3]]","[[riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input]]","[[hoverboard-bldc-hub-motor-250w-36v-with-hall-sensors]]","[[arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts]]","[[arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b]]","[[esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3]]","[[raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3]]"],"alternative_to":["[[hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based]] (BSS138-based — slower but more robust for I2C pull-up lines)"],"used_in":[],"warnings":["Does NOT work well with I2C — the auto-direction sensing conflicts with I2C open-drain pull-ups. Use BSS138-based shifter (HW-221) for I2C instead","MUST have 0.1uF decoupling capacitors on BOTH VCCA and VCCB, as close to pins as possible — without them, signal integrity degrades badly","OE pin must be connected to VCCA or driven HIGH — if left floating, outputs are disabled","NEVER connect 36V motor battery to VCCB — maximum is 5.5V. Use the +5V output from the RioRand controller","Auto-direction sensing means the direction is determined by which side drives first — works great for push-pull signals, unreliable for open-drain (I2C)"],"datasheet_url":"https://www.ti.com/product/TXS0108E"},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"docs/parts/txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction.md"},"smart_blocks:docs/parts/txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"igi4v8","at":1776210602018},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.07595065,-0.01859762,0.02490837,-0.03800222,-0.03329363,-0.0044038,0.01719385,0.01412147,-0.01046943,0.02429373,0.01021866,-0.07206557,0.00104568,0.02281595,0.03068824,-0.01714173,-0.00248285,-0.00798118,0.07193797,0.03889883,0.09630509,-0.03697513,-0.00580537,0.01258263,0.07401876,0.03593562,0.01650488,-0.0348102,-0.01908592,-0.20342413,0.01138602,-0.00385694,-0.00608557,-0.05964657,-0.03532477,-0.07269566,-0.07367832,-0.03551129,-0.02271954,-0.02359316,-0.00772359,0.01917918,-0.004